1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,545
(dramatic music)

2
00:00:22,897 --> 00:00:24,482
What are you doing on my laptop?

3
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:31,740
I was checking
if you had any naughty videos.

4
00:00:32,115 --> 00:00:32,991
Got a problem?

5
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:37,912
Donghyeon asked me to send him
something from your laptop.

6
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:40,874
You could've asked me.

7
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:43,877
He said it was really urgent.

8
00:00:46,046 --> 00:00:47,130
(sighs)

9
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:56,097
EUNSOO: I have something to ask you.

10
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,517
What is it?

11
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:03,897
It's about your crush.

12
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,358
(emotive music)

13
00:01:09,527 --> 00:01:10,737
About Jennifer.

14
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:18,119
When did you start liking her?

15
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:23,875
Do I have to tell you?

16
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:28,546
(emotive music continues)

17
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:31,049
Why did you start liking her?

18
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:36,846
(emotive music)

19
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:41,559
-Are you really going to tell her?
-Eunsoo.

20
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:44,187
SUNWOO: Please stop.

21
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:47,565
Just let me handle it myself.

22
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,986
(emotive music continues)

23
00:02:06,918 --> 00:02:08,920
(theme music)

24
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:34,779
MALE SINGER (in English): ♪ My love ♪

25
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:35,864
EPISODE 3

26
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:40,160
(in Korean) ♪ You protect me ♪

27
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:46,207
♪ You don't know that you do ♪

28
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:50,003
(in English) ♪ My love ♪

29
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:55,133
(in Korean) ♪ When I see sadness
in your eyes ♪

30
00:02:55,425 --> 00:02:58,595
♪ I feel uneasy... ♪

31
00:02:58,678 --> 00:03:00,680
WANT TO BE JOBLESS?
SQUEEZE IT OUT. YOU CAN DO IT.

32
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:03,308
YOUR LYRICS WILL MAKE IT COMPLETE.
RIGHT? PULL YOURSELF TOGETHER

33
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:10,148
-♪ I'm in love ♪
-(rasping)

34
00:03:10,231 --> 00:03:16,237
♪ I'm searching for you ♪

35
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:21,075
-(muffled music on headphones)
-♪ Love, like the wind ♪

36
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:25,496
-♪ Caresses my ears ♪
-(sighs)

37
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:28,124
(in English) ♪ I love you ♪

38
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:32,045
♪ I need you ♪

39
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:35,340
(in Korean) ♪ I've fallen for you ♪

40
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:36,591
(music ends)

41
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:38,927
(whimsical music)

42
00:03:39,677 --> 00:03:40,511
(object clatters)

43
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:43,181
Where was it...

44
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,143
(clatters)

45
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,358
EUNSOO'S LYRICS NOTEBOOK
DO NOT OPEN, ESPECIALLY SUNWOO!

46
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:55,360
(page riffling)

47
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,657
EUNSOO: What is this?
(chuckling)

48
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:04,994
(whimsical music continues)

49
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:09,874
IDIOT

50
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:13,753
(music stops)

51
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:20,677
WE WEAVE THE THREADS OF OUR TIME AGAIN

52
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:23,137
YELLOW FRIENDSHIP SAYS
IT CHEERS FOR GREEN DREAMS

53
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,515
(whimsical music)

54
00:04:27,475 --> 00:04:29,978
HIGH SCHOOL
MATH

55
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:36,109
(page riffles)

56
00:04:38,069 --> 00:04:39,070
(object clatters)

57
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:44,826
(Sunwoo sighs)

58
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:51,666
(whimsical music continues)

59
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,092
(both sigh)

60
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:03,011
(mouthing) Just once.

61
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:07,390
(paper rustles)

62
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:09,475
I'M HUNGRY

63
00:05:10,601 --> 00:05:12,312
EUNSOO: When are you getting
your phone back?

64
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:14,689
I have no idea.

65
00:05:14,772 --> 00:05:15,982
It's so inconvenient.

66
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:19,485
So why did you take pictures
with your phone everywhere

67
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:23,323
when you're supposed to be studying?
You weren't studying earlier, were you?

68
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:26,659
I hope you get all fat
and bloated tomorrow.

69
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:27,910
That's not going to happen.

70
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:28,828
(chuckles)

71
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:34,375
(slurps, munches)

72
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,502
(emotive music)

73
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:37,503
Here.

74
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:41,132
-What's this?
-My mom gave me her camera,

75
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:42,717
but I don't use it. You can have it.

76
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:44,761
Why should I?

77
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,637
It's an investment.

78
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:48,973
-An investment?
-EUNSOO: Yeah.

79
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,185
I see your potential.

80
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,145
When you become a famous photographer,

81
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:55,855
I'm going to mooch off of you
all the time.

82
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:58,483
I'm sowing the seeds early.

83
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,318
(scoffs)

84
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,321
(emotive music continues)

85
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:06,699
Thanks.

86
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:07,992
(chuckles)

87
00:06:08,576 --> 00:06:12,663
I tried writing some lyrics
while thinking about our friendship.

88
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:14,082
EUNSOO: Give it a listen.

89
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:19,045
"We weave the threads of our time again."

90
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,131
Threads?

91
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,556
(no audible dialogue)

92
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:34,227
"Yellow friendship says..."

93
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,228
(camera shutter clicks)

94
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:38,439
(exhales)

95
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:39,357
(sucks teeth)

96
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:41,359
-That was me.
-No, it wasn't.

97
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,319
-You did.
-No, I took a photo of your notebook.

98
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:44,570
I'm sure it was me.

99
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:46,030
Let's try it again.

100
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:48,950
EUSNOO: I gave it to you for a reason.

101
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:53,287
Look. From now on,
take photos of me with that.

102
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:54,747
Now. Like this.

103
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:55,832
Take it now.

104
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:57,083
(camera clicks)

105
00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:59,085
-(camera shutter clicks)
-(music stops)

106
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:06,134
What do you mean?

107
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,720
The Benzema Lauren?

108
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:11,639
The Benzema Lauren we know?

109
00:07:12,181 --> 00:07:13,516
Benzema Lauren...

110
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:15,226
With me?

111
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:16,561
Why?

112
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:17,603
DONGHYEON: Sunwoo,

113
00:07:18,146 --> 00:07:20,356
has the day finally come
for me to mooch off of you?

114
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:23,234
Will you let me?

115
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:28,781
Sunwoo, we did it!

116
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:31,576
-Wait. When did they reach out?
-DONGHYEON: Earlier!

117
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:34,036
His agent contacted the gallery directly!
Benzema Lauren!

118
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:37,123
He was really impressed with your work.

119
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:41,002
He wants to commit the next year
to collaborate with you.

120
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,129
(uplifting piano music)

121
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,338
(sighs)

122
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:46,883
Han Sunwoo.

123
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:51,846
Congratulations. I knew you had it in you.

124
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:56,392
You'll do it, right? Yes!

125
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:59,145
Of course, I don't even have to ask.
You have to, no matter what!

126
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:01,355
This is a chance
to make your name known in the world

127
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:02,940
and for me to get to the next level.

128
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:04,358
Wait a second.

129
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:09,447
To make this work, we might have
to leave Korea sooner than planned.

130
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:11,449
Let me see...

131
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:15,912
-(mouse clicking)
-We might have to leave this week.

132
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:19,665
Wait a minute.
You should get yourself ready.

133
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:23,461
(pensive music)

134
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,511
GRAPE JUICE

135
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,054
It's grape this time.

136
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:36,265
I'm really fine with anything.

137
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,268
If it's something
to make you smash it with your fist,

138
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,103
-you're not fine with it.
-(chuckles)

139
00:08:42,063 --> 00:08:44,732
I'm sorry. I should have asked you first.

140
00:08:44,815 --> 00:08:47,902
I just want to share the things I like
with the people I like,

141
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,403
and I tend to get ahead of myself.

142
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:50,655
I understand.

143
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:54,909
My mom keeps sending me mandarins
because she loves them.

144
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,035
(laughs)

145
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,457
I read your new lyrics.

146
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,000
(exclaims)

147
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:07,713
(Wooil sighs)

148
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:09,632
(inhales)

149
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:11,634
Why do you get so nervous every time?

150
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:15,096
Uh...

151
00:09:16,305 --> 00:09:17,890
Because I'm the one getting evaluated.

152
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,435
The one who does the evaluating
wouldn't know.

153
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,521
You're doing great.

154
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:26,774
And you'll keep getting better.

155
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:29,735
(paper riffles)

156
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:31,362
WOOIL: What are you doing tomorrow?

157
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,155
EUNSOO: Tomorrow?

158
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:35,700
I'm supposed to meet with Jay Jun
tomorrow evening.

159
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:38,661
It'd be nice for you two to get close
before the recording.

160
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:42,957
If you're free,
join us for dinner tomorrow.

161
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:46,586
Sure.

162
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:48,087
Okay.

163
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,130
(Eunsoo yelping)

164
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:51,007
Gosh. What did you just smash?

165
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:52,800
-I'm so sorry about this.
-I'm sorry.

166
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:55,469
-Meeting Jay Jun? You?
-Yes.

167
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:57,847
I will be granted an audience

168
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:00,016
-with the artist of all artists!
-Oh, my gosh!

169
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,101
EUNSOO: I'm so nervous.

170
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:03,728
Honey, get her some braised short ribs,

171
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:07,106
-so she can calm down.
-Eunsoo, calm down and have a drink.

172
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:08,065
Hmm.

173
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:11,360
Where's your best friend
on this monumental night?

174
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:13,821
-Sunwoo?
-Yeah.

175
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:16,032
I haven't told him yet.

176
00:10:16,699 --> 00:10:17,700
Why not?

177
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:19,035
(chuckles awkwardly)

178
00:10:20,244 --> 00:10:22,038
(light music plays on background)

179
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:23,414
Mari.

180
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:28,628
How long were you friends with Gyeolhan?

181
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:31,005
Let's see now...

182
00:10:32,006 --> 00:10:32,923
Fifteen years.

183
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:34,842
And married for eight.

184
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:37,428
Jeez, a disgustingly long time.

185
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:38,763
♪ Dashing through the snow ♪

186
00:10:38,846 --> 00:10:40,973
-(chuckles)
-GYEOLHAN: ♪ In a one-horse open sleigh ♪

187
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:45,269
How did you marry someone
that's been your friend for 15 years?

188
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:47,188
You get married when you get knocked up.

189
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:49,607
I mean,

190
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:52,360
how do you get knocked up by your friend?

191
00:10:52,943 --> 00:10:54,070
Eunsoo.

192
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:55,905
First, you get a room.

193
00:10:56,781 --> 00:11:00,409
-Then you wash up cleaner than usual.
-Jeez.

194
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:02,745
I take that back.
You don't have time to wash up.

195
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:03,663
(Mari chuckles)

196
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:05,122
Why not?

197
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:07,041
Yesterday's enemy can be a friend today.

198
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:10,461
We can be indifferent in the morning
and in love in the evening.

199
00:11:10,544 --> 00:11:11,879
Exactly.

200
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:14,465
(chuckles softly)

201
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,467
-I see.
-GYEOLJAN: But why do you ask?

202
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:19,011
Did Sunwoo say that he likes you?

203
00:11:21,305 --> 00:11:26,310
What? So he finally told you?
How wonderful!

204
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,020
That's not what happened.

205
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:29,313
Huh?

206
00:11:29,397 --> 00:11:30,231
What, then?

207
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:32,525
You two knew?

208
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:34,652
What? You didn't know?

209
00:11:34,735 --> 00:11:36,278
(Gyeolhan gasps)
How could you not know?

210
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,279
(Mari gasps)

211
00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:40,741
You can tell just by the way
he looks at you. We all knew.

212
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:43,828
Even these chopsticks here knew.
You're the only one who didn't know.

213
00:11:44,745 --> 00:11:46,997
This is a good opportunity
for you to start thinking.

214
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:48,791
-Mr. Han is handsome.
-Right.

215
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:50,209
-He's a great catch.
-Right.

216
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:52,253
-He's a rare breed.
-That's right.

217
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:55,423
You're right.

218
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:57,967
He really is a rare breed.

219
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:03,639
He feels bad all-day
for accidentally stepping on an ant.

220
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:06,350
He spends all winter worrying
about every stray cat in the world.

221
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:10,855
Every time we eat cold noodles,
he always gives me the egg, you know?

222
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:12,606
Because I love boiled eggs.

223
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:14,817
(clears throat)

224
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:17,653
-I wouldn't give you mine.
-Jeez.

225
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:21,866
I spent two-thirds of my life
with a guy like that.

226
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:24,660
And that...

227
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:26,704
(pensive music)

228
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:28,164
...makes me so upset

229
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:31,667
and scared.

230
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:35,546
I'm afraid I might hurt him.

231
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:40,342
I can't risk hurting Sunwoo...

232
00:12:44,805 --> 00:12:46,932
because he means a lot to me.

233
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,985
(pensive music continues)

234
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:05,826
(music building)

235
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,711
(pensive music)

236
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:21,759
(door opens)

237
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:34,396
(gasps)
Oh, gosh!

238
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,028
I'm not mad anymore.

239
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:43,781
How about you?

240
00:13:48,202 --> 00:13:50,287
(emotive music)

241
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:54,208
Sorry about yesterday.

242
00:13:58,629 --> 00:13:59,588
(music fades)

243
00:14:01,048 --> 00:14:02,675
SUNWOO: I shouldn't have reacted
like that...

244
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,224
(paper rustles)

245
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:12,142
(in English) Okay.

246
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,186
(in Korean) We're all good.

247
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:15,813
(chuckles)

248
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:18,482
I'm sorry too.

249
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:21,944
It was inconsiderate of me to pry.

250
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:25,823
(exhales sharply)

251
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:30,494
It's eight years ago.

252
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:35,958
You asked me when I started liking her.

253
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:38,043
It's been eight years.

254
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,465
(emotive music)

255
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:46,010
It's been that long?

256
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:48,387
Yeah.

257
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:52,057
SUNWOO: Perhaps it may have been
even longer.

258
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:57,897
It was eight years ago when I realized
that I was already in love with her.

259
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,108
(emotive music continues)

260
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,529
What was the next question?

261
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:09,199
Why did I start liking her?

262
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:14,872
Aside from my mother,
she's the only one who believes in me.

263
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:17,416
No matter what I have done or will do.

264
00:15:18,042 --> 00:15:19,919
She always says I'm the best.

265
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:23,213
(emotive music)

266
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:27,927
(inhales)
The third question.

267
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:32,514
Am I really going to tell her?

268
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:37,686
Yes.

269
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:40,981
I'm going to tell her.

270
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:50,157
-(music stops)
-(birds chirping)

271
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:55,287
(breathes deeply)

272
00:16:00,334 --> 00:16:03,128
(crockery clanging)

273
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:05,506
(exhales sharply)

274
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:10,844
(sizzling)

275
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:12,262
(exclaims)

276
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:15,933
(door creaks)

277
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:24,775
(sighs)

278
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:35,577
(door opens)

279
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:44,628
-SUNWOO: Heading out?
-Goodness!

280
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:47,256
-(Sunwoo grunts)
-(Eunsoo exhales sharply)

281
00:16:47,589 --> 00:16:48,549
Yeah.

282
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:49,591
(scoffs)

283
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:52,052
You were still...

284
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:55,431
at home. I see.

285
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:56,432
(chuckles awkwardly)

286
00:16:57,016 --> 00:17:00,394
Goodness, I can already see you
freezing later at night.

287
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:03,397
You should start wearing these.

288
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:05,357
-No. You'll be cold.
-I'm sweating now.

289
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:06,775
I can do it myself.

290
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:10,154
(sucks teeth, clears throat)

291
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:12,740
EUNSOO: What were you up to?

292
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,116
Fixing your bike.

293
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,659
(grunts)

294
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:17,453
It's so old.

295
00:17:17,911 --> 00:17:19,371
Leave it, I'll throw it away later.

296
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:22,791
Throw it away?

297
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,585
You loved this bike.

298
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,296
I did, but what can I do when it's broken?

299
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:29,339
EUNSOO: I don't ride it anyway.

300
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:32,634
(emotive music)

301
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:35,721
I should get going.

302
00:17:35,804 --> 00:17:37,014
-Eunsoo!
-Yeah?

303
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,183
When will you be home?

304
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,142
What?

305
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:43,771
-Today...
-Today!

306
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,606
I'll be home late.

307
00:17:45,814 --> 00:17:47,900
Super late.
I'm having dinner with work people.

308
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:49,026
But today...

309
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:50,861
EUNSOO: I might do
some more work after that.

310
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:54,198
I'm going to be so late.
I might even see the sunrise.

311
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:57,076
So go to bed. Okay?

312
00:17:57,159 --> 00:17:58,160
I'm going now!

313
00:17:58,243 --> 00:17:59,453
I have something...

314
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,123
to tell you.

315
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:09,296
HWASIN MUSIC
JAY JUN

316
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:12,132
(scribbling)

317
00:18:12,382 --> 00:18:13,842
(slurps, chuckles)

318
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:15,719
You're getting nervous again.

319
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:18,055
(chuckles)

320
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:19,264
(door opens)

321
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:22,643
-Welcome.
-WOOIL: Oh, you're here.

322
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:23,977
-Jay Jun.
-Hello.

323
00:18:24,061 --> 00:18:26,939
-Hello.
-It's been a while. How have you been?

324
00:18:27,022 --> 00:18:28,857
-Hello...
-Let me introduce you.

325
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:32,528
This is our lyricist for the new single,
Ms. Lee Eunsoo.

326
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,197
And this is his manager. and his CEO,

327
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:37,366
and, as you already know, Jay Jun.

328
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:39,076
Hello.

329
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:42,079
Pleased to meet you.
I heard a lot about you.

330
00:18:42,162 --> 00:18:43,163
Yes.

331
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:45,582
(laughing)

332
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:49,336
-We had to grab a taxi then.
-WOOIL: I'm sorry.

333
00:18:49,419 --> 00:18:50,462
(group laughing)

334
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:52,965
-Sorry about that!
-CEO: The cab fare was really high.

335
00:18:53,048 --> 00:18:56,093
You know,
we were all so curious about you.

336
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,469
About me?

337
00:18:57,928 --> 00:19:00,639
-We were all shocked to see that you...
-Hey.

338
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:01,598
(chuckles)

339
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:04,434
That you were even prettier
than Mr. Kang had described.

340
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:07,938
We all thought you were a trainee
next in line to debut as a K-pop idol.

341
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:12,526
He spoke so highly of you.
That he found an amazing lyricist.

342
00:19:12,609 --> 00:19:14,194
-CEO: Right.
-Yes.

343
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:19,575
He insists that we need your lyrics
for Jay Jun's album to be a hit.

344
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:21,368
Who does he think he is, the singer?

345
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:23,662
(group laughing)

346
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:26,832
Ms. Lee, you have to do a great job.

347
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,333
We're all expecting a lot from you.

348
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,460
Stop giving her pressure.

349
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:32,087
You have to watch out for these people.

350
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,923
They're always scheming about
how they can get something out of us.

351
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:38,468
Don't be so harsh on us who meekly wait
to be graced with your songs.

352
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,554
-Hey, let's drink, just us.
-Sure.

353
00:19:40,637 --> 00:19:42,764
-Cheers!
-There he goes again.

354
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:44,016
-I'm just kidding!
-Cheers!

355
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:45,142
Well, thanks a lot.

356
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:47,227
-We're in your care.
-You should watch out for him.

357
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:48,145
No way.

358
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:54,276
(pensive music)

359
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:59,114
INTERNATIONAL LANDSCAPE PHOTOGRAPHY
OF THE YEAR AWARDS WINNER

360
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:01,783
MARINE CONSERVATION PHOTO GRAND PRIZE
YOUNG ADULT PHOTOGRAPHER'S AWARD...

361
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:05,329
(tapping)

362
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:17,758
(pensive music continues)

363
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:26,683
(page riffles)

364
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,610
(pensive music continues)

365
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:50,582
(cellphone clatters)

366
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:52,834
(page riffles)

367
00:20:54,002 --> 00:20:55,337
(exhales sharply)

368
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,802
(tapping)

369
00:21:02,886 --> 00:21:03,929
(sighs)

370
00:21:05,931 --> 00:21:08,267
-Bye.
-Dinner was great!

371
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:10,352
-Great job today.
-Jun, keep your voice in shape.

372
00:21:10,435 --> 00:21:11,937
-I'll get going. I'll call you later.
-Okay.

373
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:14,147
-I was going to treat you all.
-It's okay, no worries.

374
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:16,566
Take care of her.
Ms. Lee, I entrust you with our song.

375
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,110
-Thank you.
-Best of luck, Ms. Lee!

376
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:20,153
Let us know
if Mr. Kang is being too hard on you.

377
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:21,863
Stop it and just leave.

378
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:23,282
Take care.

379
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:28,161
Gosh, that was hectic.
(chuckles)

380
00:21:28,829 --> 00:21:30,205
Enough to sober me up.

381
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:31,373
(chuckles)

382
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:33,292
Do you want to go for another round?

383
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:36,628
There's a really nice wine bar
on the first floor of the studio building.

384
00:21:37,379 --> 00:21:38,255
Ah...

385
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:39,756
Wine?

386
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,883
Their carpaccio is a work of culinary art.

387
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:43,176
It pairs perfectly with wine.

388
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:45,429
Let's go.

389
00:21:45,762 --> 00:21:46,680
(Wooil chuckles)

390
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,184
(rattling)

391
00:21:59,693 --> 00:22:00,610
(brake squeaks)

392
00:22:00,944 --> 00:22:01,903
(sighs)

393
00:22:03,196 --> 00:22:04,072
(metal clanks)

394
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:22,257
(cellphone beeps)

395
00:22:22,883 --> 00:22:26,553
(phone line ringing)

396
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:30,557
(phone line ringing continues)

397
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:33,393
FEMALE OPERATOR: The person you're calling
is unavailable...

398
00:22:38,607 --> 00:22:40,525
(exhales sharply)

399
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:48,700
WOOIL: How is it? Really good, isn't it?

400
00:22:49,451 --> 00:22:52,287
It is. It's my first time trying.

401
00:22:53,455 --> 00:22:56,124
I've tried different places,
but this place has the best carpaccio.

402
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:57,876
(classical music plays on background)

403
00:22:57,959 --> 00:22:59,628
And the best selection of pinot noir.

404
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:02,339
I'm glad you like it.

405
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:04,216
(chuckles)

406
00:23:06,843 --> 00:23:07,677
By the way,

407
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:12,808
what the CEO said earlier...

408
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:16,061
Oh, I'm sorry.

409
00:23:16,311 --> 00:23:17,813
WOOIL: I didn't mean to pressure you.

410
00:23:19,147 --> 00:23:20,148
But...

411
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:21,483
Mm...

412
00:23:22,192 --> 00:23:25,487
I told them that because
I truly believe you are a good lyricist.

413
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:26,863
And...

414
00:23:27,697 --> 00:23:32,077
The day you pleaded with me
to give you two more weeks...

415
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:35,914
To be honest, you were so beautiful.

416
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:43,463
How nervous you were about changing
even a single letter of your lyrics...

417
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:46,007
It was just beautiful.

418
00:23:48,176 --> 00:23:50,637
To see a beautiful person work
with a passion for what she does.

419
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:55,434
(sucks teeth)

420
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:58,311
Gosh. So this is how it feels.

421
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:00,105
Sorry?

422
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:02,149
To become the evaluated.

423
00:24:02,649 --> 00:24:05,152
It really is nerve-racking.

424
00:24:07,529 --> 00:24:09,614
The one who does the evaluating
wouldn't know, right?

425
00:24:11,074 --> 00:24:11,992
(chuckles softly)

426
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:14,494
You don't need to say anything right now.

427
00:24:15,162 --> 00:24:16,329
Let's take it slow.

428
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:19,749
Both work and getting to know each other.

429
00:24:21,543 --> 00:24:22,377
Okay.

430
00:24:25,422 --> 00:24:26,840
(engine rumbling)

431
00:24:28,884 --> 00:24:30,844
-SUNWOO: Thank you.
-DRIVER: No problem.

432
00:24:31,887 --> 00:24:34,931
VACANT

433
00:24:35,015 --> 00:24:36,766
(engine revs)

434
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:49,988
There's a really unique wine bar
we should try next time.

435
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:51,615
Right by the Cheongdam Intersection...

436
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:52,699
SUNWOO: Eunsoo!

437
00:24:53,783 --> 00:24:55,702
What are the chances?

438
00:24:57,037 --> 00:24:58,455
What are you doing here?

439
00:24:58,538 --> 00:25:00,957
I walked in to buy a bottle of wine
for Donghyeon.

440
00:25:01,666 --> 00:25:03,168
SUNWOO: He has good news to celebrate.

441
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:04,503
Hello.

442
00:25:06,004 --> 00:25:08,256
Oh, right. Hello.

443
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,299
(Sunwoo chuckles)

444
00:25:09,382 --> 00:25:11,760
So you buy your bottles at a wine bar
and not a store.

445
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:13,178
How unique.

446
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:14,304
(Eunsoo chuckles awkwardly)

447
00:25:14,804 --> 00:25:18,892
I wanted to pick one
that pairs well with food.

448
00:25:19,142 --> 00:25:21,102
-Yeah.
-I see.

449
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:23,188
Is this good?

450
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:26,983
-(slurps)
-(clanks)

451
00:25:28,109 --> 00:25:29,361
(munches)

452
00:25:31,321 --> 00:25:32,239
Not bad.

453
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:33,281
(chuckles)

454
00:25:34,157 --> 00:25:36,243
-Would you like me to order you some more?
-I'm fine.

455
00:25:37,452 --> 00:25:39,538
(classical music playing)

456
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:47,629
(cellphone buzzing)

457
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:50,924
Mr. Kang.

458
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:54,010
-Yes?
-I need to make a phone call.

459
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,053
Of course.

460
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:56,555
(chair scrapes)

461
00:26:00,016 --> 00:26:02,477
(retreating footsteps)

462
00:26:08,441 --> 00:26:10,569
(slow, tense music)

463
00:26:20,787 --> 00:26:23,039
(tense music continues)

464
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,047
(Wooil grunts)

465
00:26:31,464 --> 00:26:32,924
She dropped this.

466
00:26:40,348 --> 00:26:42,392
(classical music playing)

467
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:46,563
I wanted to thank you for last time.

468
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:48,940
About what?

469
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:52,277
Thanks to you, I was able
to learn a thing about her tastes.

470
00:26:53,528 --> 00:26:54,362
Mandarins.

471
00:26:54,613 --> 00:26:55,488
(scoffs)

472
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:56,865
Ah...

473
00:26:57,365 --> 00:26:58,241
I see.

474
00:26:58,575 --> 00:26:59,534
(groans)

475
00:27:01,453 --> 00:27:02,454
(Sunwoo sighs)

476
00:27:05,498 --> 00:27:07,500
I just told her that I liked her.

477
00:27:10,587 --> 00:27:12,130
WOOIL: I'm not going to pressure her.

478
00:27:12,213 --> 00:27:13,715
I'll take it slow and get to know her.

479
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:17,177
(emotive music)

480
00:27:20,722 --> 00:27:21,765
(slurps)

481
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:24,309
(glass clanks)

482
00:27:33,109 --> 00:27:34,194
Is this any good?

483
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:36,821
It's good for a gift.

484
00:27:37,322 --> 00:27:38,907
WOOIL: It's a pinot noir from France.

485
00:27:39,449 --> 00:27:42,327
A good amount of tannins.

486
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:44,162
Was Eunsoo enjoying this?

487
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:48,041
Yes. She seemed to like it.

488
00:27:51,795 --> 00:27:54,631
(footsteps approaching)

489
00:27:55,632 --> 00:27:57,008
EUNSOO (whispers): I'm sorry.

490
00:27:58,134 --> 00:28:00,220
(emotive music continues)

491
00:28:06,643 --> 00:28:07,727
(slurps)

492
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:13,316
Shall we call it a night?
I feel a bit dizzy.

493
00:28:13,983 --> 00:28:17,237
Dizzy? Then I'll call a chauffeur for us.

494
00:28:17,612 --> 00:28:19,155
Where do you live?

495
00:28:19,489 --> 00:28:21,700
WOOIL: We can drop you off on the way
to take Eunsoo home.

496
00:28:21,783 --> 00:28:23,243
It's okay. We'll get ourselves home.

497
00:28:23,326 --> 00:28:26,413
You can go ahead.
I have another appointment to get to.

498
00:28:26,830 --> 00:28:27,956
Please take her home safely.

499
00:28:28,498 --> 00:28:29,582
(reflective music)

500
00:28:29,666 --> 00:28:30,792
Where are you...

501
00:28:31,418 --> 00:28:32,252
WOOIL: Eunsoo.

502
00:28:33,336 --> 00:28:34,170
Shall we?

503
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:38,216
Okay.

504
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:41,553
EUNSOO: Thank you.

505
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:43,638
WOOIL: Take care, Eunsoo.

506
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:46,182
-Thank you. You too, Mr. Kang.
-WOOIL: Bye.

507
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:47,809
-WOOIL: See you next week.
-Thank you.

508
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:51,604
(engine revving)

509
00:28:55,442 --> 00:28:57,652
(reflective music continues)

510
00:29:08,455 --> 00:29:10,540
(reflective music)

511
00:29:32,937 --> 00:29:35,607
(reflective music continues)

512
00:29:46,201 --> 00:29:48,411
(reflective music)

513
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:58,755
SUNWOO: Am I really going to tell her?

514
00:30:02,091 --> 00:30:02,926
Yes.

515
00:30:04,469 --> 00:30:05,762
I'm going to tell her.

516
00:30:08,681 --> 00:30:10,433
(music fades)

517
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:20,777
CONTACTS
FAVORITES, SUNWOO

518
00:30:25,031 --> 00:30:27,075
(light music)

519
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:31,412
(cellphone beeps)

520
00:30:32,956 --> 00:30:36,209
FEMALE OPERATOR: The phone is turned off.
You will be directed to voicemail.

521
00:30:36,334 --> 00:30:38,795
Charges will apply after the tone.

522
00:30:38,878 --> 00:30:41,172
(light music continues)

523
00:30:44,133 --> 00:30:46,219
(cellphone clatters)

524
00:30:51,099 --> 00:30:53,268
(light music)

525
00:30:58,064 --> 00:31:00,483
Hey, Eunsoo. Good to see you too.

526
00:31:03,069 --> 00:31:03,987
Where's Sunwoo?

527
00:31:04,696 --> 00:31:05,780
He left a while ago.

528
00:31:07,657 --> 00:31:08,491
He did?

529
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:12,537
Oh, right. Here you go.

530
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:18,751
Chocolate? For what?

531
00:31:18,835 --> 00:31:21,796
Sunwoo told me yesterday
that you had some good news to celebrate.

532
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,172
EUNSOO: What's the good news?

533
00:31:23,339 --> 00:31:24,173
Good news?

534
00:31:25,341 --> 00:31:27,844
Yes, I have good news.

535
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:31,347
But Sunwoo is the one
who needs to celebrate, not me.

536
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:33,182
Cuba?

537
00:31:33,892 --> 00:31:34,767
For how long?

538
00:31:34,851 --> 00:31:37,812
At least a year in South America.

539
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:39,647
DONGHYEON: Then probably Europe
after that.

540
00:31:39,981 --> 00:31:41,608
We'll go all over Europe.

541
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:43,192
Ah...

542
00:31:45,278 --> 00:31:46,404
Donghyeon.

543
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:48,531
How big is this

544
00:31:49,532 --> 00:31:51,034
opportunity for him?

545
00:31:51,534 --> 00:31:54,245
It's an opportunity
to change the course of his entire life.

546
00:31:54,329 --> 00:31:58,124
One exhibition with this guy means
getting his name known worldwide.

547
00:31:58,833 --> 00:32:02,045
Sunwoo will become
a world-famous photographer.

548
00:32:03,713 --> 00:32:04,631
(Donghyeon groans)

549
00:32:05,465 --> 00:32:06,382
(clatters)

550
00:32:10,219 --> 00:32:11,596
Did you not know at all?

551
00:32:12,805 --> 00:32:14,015
Did Sunwoo not tell you?

552
00:32:14,891 --> 00:32:15,850
No.

553
00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:18,019
-(grunts)
-(rustles)

554
00:32:19,979 --> 00:32:21,064
No way.

555
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:24,067
It can't be. No.

556
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:25,610
No. It can't be!

557
00:32:25,693 --> 00:32:26,986
It cannot be it!

558
00:32:27,487 --> 00:32:28,321
(blows air)

559
00:32:28,404 --> 00:32:29,322
Hey.

560
00:32:30,990 --> 00:32:34,953
Have you heard anything shocking
from Sunwoo?

561
00:32:35,662 --> 00:32:38,790
Anything to startle you,
to make your heart skip a beat,

562
00:32:38,873 --> 00:32:41,501
or to make you feel jolts of electricity
throughout your body?

563
00:32:41,584 --> 00:32:43,711
Did Sunwoo make you feel
anything like that at all?

564
00:32:45,338 --> 00:32:46,297
No.

565
00:32:46,381 --> 00:32:47,215
Really?

566
00:32:53,054 --> 00:32:54,389
-(paper rustles)
-(Donghyeon sobs)

567
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:56,224
What's wrong with you? Are you crying?

568
00:32:56,349 --> 00:32:57,517
DONGHYEON: No, I'm fine.

569
00:32:58,017 --> 00:33:00,436
If you do hear anything from him,

570
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:03,189
please call me right away. Okay?

571
00:33:03,564 --> 00:33:05,191
-(cellphone buzzing)
-Okay.

572
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:08,653
Hello, sir.

573
00:33:10,363 --> 00:33:11,864
Oh, you've heard?

574
00:33:12,448 --> 00:33:14,867
Sunwoo only has good things
waiting for him now.

575
00:33:15,451 --> 00:33:17,453
DONGHYEON: We'll definitely be going!

576
00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:19,414
I'm so happy it's making me tear up.

577
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:21,457
-(door closes)
-(reflective music)

578
00:33:28,631 --> 00:33:30,717
(reflective music continues)

579
00:33:37,849 --> 00:33:38,850
(Eunsoo sighs)

580
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:48,067
What are you doing?

581
00:33:51,988 --> 00:33:52,989
Ta-da.

582
00:33:53,740 --> 00:33:54,866
It's all fixed up.

583
00:33:58,703 --> 00:33:59,996
SUNWOO: It's your first bike.

584
00:34:01,289 --> 00:34:02,832
And I taught you how to ride with this.

585
00:34:03,583 --> 00:34:06,294
I couldn't throw away something
that held some of our fondest memories.

586
00:34:08,004 --> 00:34:09,005
It's my gift to you.

587
00:34:10,131 --> 00:34:11,090
Thanks.

588
00:34:12,341 --> 00:34:13,426
It looks brand new.

589
00:34:14,802 --> 00:34:16,137
I didn't paint this part.

590
00:34:17,847 --> 00:34:18,931
Why not?

591
00:34:19,015 --> 00:34:20,600
It's where I used to grab for you.

592
00:34:21,392 --> 00:34:23,394
I just want you to remember me
every time you see it.

593
00:34:26,397 --> 00:34:28,816
(reflective music)

594
00:34:31,527 --> 00:34:32,528
Eunsoo.

595
00:34:33,321 --> 00:34:34,739
-I...
-Sunwoo.

596
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:36,324
(music stops)

597
00:34:37,825 --> 00:34:41,621
Do you remember what I said
when I first gave you your camera?

598
00:34:42,997 --> 00:34:46,209
I wanted you to become
a famous photographer and thrive.

599
00:34:47,335 --> 00:34:48,836
I even wrote lyrics about it.

600
00:34:50,129 --> 00:34:54,383
That yellow friendship
cheers for green dreams.

601
00:34:57,970 --> 00:35:02,683
I've always believed
you were better than the likes of me.

602
00:35:07,146 --> 00:35:09,732
EUNSOO: My yellow friendship
will always be on your side.

603
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:12,276
Because we're friends.

604
00:35:14,695 --> 00:35:16,447
That's how I feel, Sunwoo.

605
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:20,368
(birds chirping)

606
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:24,163
Can I speak now?

607
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:27,375
SUNWOO: Lee Eunsoo.

608
00:35:30,378 --> 00:35:31,337
Goodbye.

609
00:35:32,046 --> 00:35:33,339
(pensive music)

610
00:35:33,756 --> 00:35:36,801
My schedule got moved up a bit,
so I'm leaving tomorrow.

611
00:35:37,635 --> 00:35:38,511
Surprised, right?

612
00:35:39,053 --> 00:35:42,390
Just as you predicted, I think I'm about
to become a totally famous photographer.

613
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:45,518
You know my favorite photographer,
Benzema Lauren?

614
00:35:46,310 --> 00:35:48,229
He wants to work with me.

615
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:50,898
(chuckles softly)

616
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:53,901
Wow. Awesome!

617
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:55,695
I'm so happy for you.

618
00:35:55,987 --> 00:35:56,988
Congratulations, Sunwoo.

619
00:35:57,071 --> 00:35:59,615
I told you. You always had it in you.

620
00:35:59,699 --> 00:36:00,741
(chuckles)

621
00:36:01,367 --> 00:36:03,411
-EUNSOO: Congratulations, really.
-Thanks.

622
00:36:06,455 --> 00:36:07,832
Sure.
(chuckles)

623
00:36:09,500 --> 00:36:11,544
(pensive music)

624
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:19,886
(pensive music continues)

625
00:36:35,109 --> 00:36:36,027
(music fades)

626
00:36:37,862 --> 00:36:39,697
(car whooshing)

627
00:36:43,659 --> 00:36:45,119
SUNWOO: You should go. It's cold.

628
00:36:45,953 --> 00:36:47,455
EUNSOO: I should see you off.

629
00:36:47,747 --> 00:36:49,207
You didn't forget anything, did you?

630
00:36:49,290 --> 00:36:51,792
-You sure your passport isn't expired?
-I'm not like you.

631
00:36:51,876 --> 00:36:52,710
Hey.

632
00:36:55,087 --> 00:36:57,089
EUNSOO: Who am I going
to hang out with now?

633
00:36:57,173 --> 00:36:59,467
You should be hanging out with that song.

634
00:36:59,550 --> 00:37:00,593
If you want to make it big.

635
00:37:01,427 --> 00:37:03,763
EUNSOO: Right. I'll get this song
ranked within the top 100.

636
00:37:04,263 --> 00:37:06,724
No, first place on the charts.

637
00:37:06,807 --> 00:37:07,642
SUNWOO: Damn, right.

638
00:37:08,059 --> 00:37:09,143
(Eunsoo chuckles softly)

639
00:37:11,437 --> 00:37:13,439
SUNWOO: I came to help you
with your lyrics,

640
00:37:14,106 --> 00:37:15,483
but we never got to finish.

641
00:37:16,859 --> 00:37:18,694
EUNSOO: Yeah, it's a shame.

642
00:37:20,112 --> 00:37:21,572
Listen to the song when it comes out.

643
00:37:25,993 --> 00:37:28,663
Don't skip meals and eat well.

644
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:33,125
And keep your neck covered
and warm. Please.

645
00:37:33,251 --> 00:37:35,336
You'll really freeze to death
trying to be fashionable.

646
00:37:35,962 --> 00:37:38,047
Gosh, all right. I heard you.

647
00:37:38,714 --> 00:37:40,383
Always nagging.

648
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:50,476
Take care of yourself.
Let's hang out when I get back.

649
00:37:57,108 --> 00:37:58,317
It reminds me of that day.

650
00:38:00,903 --> 00:38:03,572
Eight years ago.
The day before you entered the military.

651
00:38:07,743 --> 00:38:08,619
(chuckles)

652
00:38:09,870 --> 00:38:10,705
Yeah.

653
00:38:16,836 --> 00:38:17,753
There's my bus.

654
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:19,880
I should go.

655
00:38:20,589 --> 00:38:21,632
Get home safe.

656
00:38:21,799 --> 00:38:22,967
(brake squeaks)

657
00:38:26,053 --> 00:38:27,638
EUNSOO: Call me when you get there.

658
00:38:27,930 --> 00:38:28,764
SUNWOO: Okay.

659
00:38:28,848 --> 00:38:30,641
(engine rumbles)

660
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:39,817
(engine revving)

661
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:54,498
(silence)

662
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:11,682
(footsteps)

663
00:39:25,613 --> 00:39:26,739
(cellphone buzzing)

664
00:39:29,992 --> 00:39:32,620
SUNWOO: I made some mandarin preserves
and left them in the kitchen cabinet.

665
00:39:33,245 --> 00:39:35,081
It should be better than plain mandarins.

666
00:39:35,915 --> 00:39:37,958
(somber music)

667
00:39:42,088 --> 00:39:43,881
SUNWOO: Don't you feel sad at all?

668
00:39:43,964 --> 00:39:45,800
Your friend of ten years
is going to the army.

669
00:39:45,883 --> 00:39:46,842
(phone camera clicks)

670
00:39:46,926 --> 00:39:48,302
To be accurate, 11 years.

671
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:50,388
And why should I?
I'll see you soon anyway.

672
00:39:51,597 --> 00:39:52,681
Two years isn't soon.

673
00:39:53,265 --> 00:39:54,392
I'm going to visit you.

674
00:39:54,809 --> 00:39:55,851
I'm going to write to you.

675
00:39:56,102 --> 00:39:57,520
You'll come out on leaves too.

676
00:39:57,603 --> 00:39:59,146
Time will fly right by.

677
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:00,481
You're so heartless.

678
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:05,486
I'll bring lots of good food when I visit.

679
00:40:10,032 --> 00:40:11,033
Good.

680
00:40:11,617 --> 00:40:14,120
Worry about yourself.
Don't skip meals and eat well.

681
00:40:14,203 --> 00:40:15,913
And keep your neck covered and warm.

682
00:40:15,996 --> 00:40:17,456
You'll freeze to death
trying to be fashionable.

683
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:19,792
All right. Stop nagging.

684
00:40:21,794 --> 00:40:23,629
See you. Now get back to work.

685
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:25,381
Okay.

686
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:28,968
Hey, Sunwoo!

687
00:40:29,969 --> 00:40:30,970
Sunwoo.

688
00:40:32,972 --> 00:40:33,973
Take care.

689
00:40:39,687 --> 00:40:42,440
-♪ Afraid you might see my tears ♪
-Oh, my.

690
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:43,774
What is this?

691
00:40:44,358 --> 00:40:46,026
♪ I cry without a sound ♪

692
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:47,903
Take care of yourself.

693
00:40:47,987 --> 00:40:50,739
-♪ But these tears of mine ♪
-SUNWOO: Let's hang out when I get back.

694
00:40:50,823 --> 00:40:52,992
♪ That fall now ♪

695
00:40:53,284 --> 00:40:54,368
Okay, let's do that.

696
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:56,495
-♪ Are tears ♪
-EUNSOO: Don't get sick.

697
00:40:56,579 --> 00:40:58,789
-♪ I can no longer hold back ♪
-You too.

698
00:40:58,873 --> 00:41:01,876
♪ Afraid this loud heart of mine ♪

699
00:41:01,959 --> 00:41:03,461
-SUNWOO: See you.
-Bye.

700
00:41:03,544 --> 00:41:06,547
♪ Is no longer a secret ♪

701
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:09,008
-See you!
-SUNWOO: Get inside, it's cold!

702
00:41:09,091 --> 00:41:10,759
♪ Embrace me a little more ♪

703
00:41:10,843 --> 00:41:12,970
♪ Talk to me a little more ♪

704
00:41:13,053 --> 00:41:16,640
♪ Don't push me away, not now ♪

705
00:41:16,724 --> 00:41:20,311
♪ So that I can see you a little more
so that I can cry a little more ♪

706
00:41:20,394 --> 00:41:23,898
♪ Before I have to let you go ♪

707
00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:27,485
♪ Just a little more, just a little ♪

708
00:41:27,568 --> 00:41:32,239
♪ I want to stand here
holding onto you a while longer ♪

709
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:37,828
♪ Until this night is no more ♪

710
00:41:37,912 --> 00:41:41,916
♪ This cold breeze
had never brought us together ♪

711
00:41:42,458 --> 00:41:45,127
♪ Afraid it will only take you
far away from me ♪

712
00:41:45,211 --> 00:41:48,881
♪ Please don't leave me ♪

713
00:41:48,964 --> 00:41:52,384
♪ I never imagined ♪

714
00:41:52,468 --> 00:41:56,972
♪ Life without you, not even for a day ♪

715
00:41:57,056 --> 00:41:59,975
♪ Please ♪

716
00:42:00,059 --> 00:42:05,898
♪ Don't leave me like this ♪

717
00:42:05,981 --> 00:42:07,107
(music fades)

718
00:42:10,736 --> 00:42:12,154
EUNSOO: My dearly missed Sunwoo.

719
00:42:14,156 --> 00:42:15,282
Maybe...

720
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:19,954
I'll be able to write
the best lyrics this time.

721
00:42:20,496 --> 00:42:22,122
(reflective music)

722
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:27,253
Because I finally understand
what you meant about unrequited love.

723
00:42:40,349 --> 00:42:41,433
(pouring liquid)

724
00:42:45,896 --> 00:42:46,772
(slurps)

725
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:56,031
Just seeing Eunsoo smile
is enough to fill my heart.

726
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:03,831
When I put a scarf around her
on a chilly day, I feel I've done my job.

727
00:43:04,748 --> 00:43:05,833
Silly, right?

728
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:07,251
(chuckles softly)

729
00:43:09,044 --> 00:43:10,879
But that really is all I need.

730
00:43:12,631 --> 00:43:14,925
I just want her to feel comfortable
around me.

731
00:43:19,513 --> 00:43:22,391
But I almost hurt her,
just to let her know how I feel.

732
00:43:23,309 --> 00:43:24,560
What was I thinking?

733
00:43:26,854 --> 00:43:28,397
-(Gyeolhan slurps)
-(sighs)

734
00:43:32,359 --> 00:43:33,569
When she cries...

735
00:43:33,694 --> 00:43:34,945
(liquid pours)

736
00:43:37,114 --> 00:43:39,241
I don't know what to do.

737
00:43:42,202 --> 00:43:43,704
(rain pattering)

738
00:43:54,214 --> 00:43:56,467
(rain pattering)

739
00:44:02,431 --> 00:44:03,682
(wind chimes tinkle)

740
00:44:19,114 --> 00:44:21,200
(romantic music)

741
00:44:22,743 --> 00:44:26,497
MALE SINGER: ♪ Whenever I see you ♪

742
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:32,920
♪ It is so strange ♪

743
00:44:33,796 --> 00:44:36,215
♪ My heart acts on its own ♪

744
00:44:36,298 --> 00:44:43,180
♪ I no longer had the confidence to love ♪

745
00:44:44,139 --> 00:44:48,644
♪ But I muster up the courage
after having met you ♪

746
00:44:50,229 --> 00:44:53,732
♪ My heart flutters ♪

747
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:56,568
-♪ Whenever I see you ♪
-She was drinking wine.

748
00:44:57,069 --> 00:45:00,531
♪ I never know what to do... ♪

749
00:45:00,906 --> 00:45:02,866
She hates wine
because it gives her a headache.

750
00:45:03,575 --> 00:45:10,582
♪ Just when I thought
I could no longer love ♪

751
00:45:10,999 --> 00:45:13,001
-But if that's what she wants...
-♪ You came to me ♪

752
00:45:13,085 --> 00:45:16,630
♪ My love ♪

753
00:45:17,214 --> 00:45:19,383
...then I will support her
with all my heart.

754
00:45:24,722 --> 00:45:30,352
♪ They say love is more than words ♪

755
00:45:31,603 --> 00:45:37,109
♪ I'll pour out my heart
more than anyone else ♪

756
00:45:37,693 --> 00:45:44,116
♪ I won't hurt your precious heart ♪

757
00:45:45,367 --> 00:45:50,706
♪ I'll protect you now ♪

758
00:45:52,332 --> 00:45:55,919
♪ I ponder how ♪

759
00:45:56,336 --> 00:45:59,631
♪ How I can comfort you ♪

760
00:45:59,715 --> 00:46:02,468
♪ When you are in need... ♪
